  <h1 class="case-study__title reveal">VRT Digital Experience</h1>
  <p class="case-study__intro reveal">
    Designing user-centered digital experiences for Flanders' public broadcaster,
    reaching millions of viewers across web, mobile, and connected TV platforms.
  </p>

  <div class="case-study__image-placeholder reveal--clip">[ Project hero image ]</div>

  <h2 class="reveal">The Challenge</h2>
  <p class="reveal">
    As a public broadcaster, VRT serves a diverse audience with varying needs and digital literacy levels.
    The challenge was to create cohesive, accessible experiences that make content discovery effortless
    while maintaining the editorial integrity that viewers trust.
  </p>

  <h2 class="reveal">My Role</h2>
  <p class="reveal">
    As UX Designer, I led user research, interaction design, and usability testing across multiple
    product teams. My work focused on understanding audience behaviour through data and research,
    then translating those insights into intuitive interfaces.
  </p>

  <div class="case-study__image-placeholder reveal--clip">[ Process / wireframes ]</div>

  <h2 class="reveal">Approach</h2>
  <p class="reveal">
    Starting from the user's perspective — always. Every design decision was grounded in research,
    whether through user interviews, analytics review, or prototype testing with real audiences.
    I worked closely with developers, product managers, and editorial teams to ensure designs
    were both feasible and aligned with content strategy.
  </p>

